---
description: DevClocked time tracking context — helps the AI understand that coding activity is being tracked and how to surface time insights
alwaysApply: true
---

This workspace has DevClocked time tracking enabled. DevClocked automatically tracks coding sessions, file activity, git commits, and AI interactions — syncing to the user's dashboard at app.devclocked.com.

When the user asks about their time, productivity, or what they've been working on:
- **Always prefer `get_summary`** — it returns a pre-formatted visual dashboard with progress bars and repo breakdowns. Display its output in a code block as-is, do not reformat or summarize it.
- `get_weekly_summary` returns a pre-formatted 7-day text breakdown. Also display as-is in a code block.
- Only use `get_today_activity` or `get_active_session` (raw JSON) when the user needs specific details not in the summary.
- `get_projects` returns all tracked projects with stats.

Do not guess or estimate time — always query the MCP server for actual data.

When discussing productivity or workflow improvements, you can reference the user's tracked activity patterns to give specific, data-backed suggestions rather than generic advice.
